        <h2>Climate</h2>
        <h4>The climate in Canada changes drastically throughout the course of a single year. In the winters, places get to -45 degrees celcius and in the summer, they get to 45 degrees celcius. The fall is often windy and dry and the spring is often wet and muddy. The best time to visit is early summer because it's not too hot and not too cold but the winters are probably the most interesting season because of the fact that going outside can kill you because of how cold it is. </h4>
        
